how do i just enjoy the present time i always have always been a planner worrier i seem to be incapable of just relaxing enjoying the present i am worrying about things that won't come into play for years to come i don't know why i'm tired of worrying about everything trying to figure everything out all the time i just want to be able to be happy with my life right now instead of wanting more and planning for the future so much does anyone have any ideas about how i can stop worrying about the future oh i do have an anxiety problem i've been on anti depressant for a while i'm a lot better than i used to be i just can't shake this planning you seem to be a thinker one who possess self awareness i recommend looking into yoga classes also seek out those who also consider similar thoughts as yours you'd be surprised also try meditative breathing concentrate on the day at hand a good planner lays out a schedule but don't be a slave to the clock take time to relax and enjoy yourself have an afternoon latte browse the books at a bookstore or go to a museum and chill with some friends there it is good to be concerned with future plans but don't let them overwhelm you good luck Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Anxiety Insomnia Meditation Avenue Q Enneagram Shaggy dog story About a Boy The Contender (television series) Charles Darwin's illness Jiddu Krishnamurti Social rule Hatha yoga Friends of the Western Buddhist Order EastEnders Psychoanalysis Tai Chi Chuan The Amazing Race Clinical depression Sigmund Freud Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb Cultural Revolution The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Mid-levels Coffee Immortality Capitalism Yoga Stress (medicine) Anapana 2000 Australian Grand Prix Kundalini Humphrey Bogart Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Raja Yoga Happiness Singlish Ludwig Wittgenstein Oh My Goddess! Reincarnation Children of Dune General anxiety disorder Nuclear warfare Baroque chess Reiki Phaedo Stoicism Theodicy Operatio